                              "type": "text",
                              "id": "bTm9w",
                              "name": "notePara1",
                              "fill": "#9CA3AF",
                              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                              "width": "fill_container",
                              "content": "The attention mechanism allows models to weigh the importance of different parts of the input sequence when producing an output. Unlike fixed-length context vectors, attention dynamically focuses on relevant tokens.",
